<p><strong>Problem:</strong> </p>  <p>When I add 'Silverlight 5' as a target to my PCL project, the compiler can no longer find System.Collections.Specialized.</p>  <p><strong>Tools:</strong></p>  <ul> <li>Visual Studio 2013</li> <li>Xamarin 3.11.837 (not sure it matters)</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Setup:</strong> </p>  <ul> <li><p>Create a new C# Portable Class Library project:</p>  <ul> <li>In Class1.cs (1-line): <code>using System.Collections.Specialized;</code></li> </ul></li> <li><p>Targets: </p>  <ul> <li>.NET 4.5; </li> <li>Windows 8; </li> <li>Windows Phone 8.1</li> </ul></li> <li><p>Add the target: </p>  <ul> <li>Go to Project->Properties->Targets</li> <li>Add "Silverlight 5" as target</li> <li><code>Specialized</code> can no longer be found.</li> </ul></li> </ul>